1
00:00:05,267 --> 00:00:06,667
<i> You're moving to Cebu?</i>

2
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:08,567
<i>We could really make it big
in Cebu.</i>

3
00:00:08,700 --> 00:00:10,600
<i>Just make sure
you don't screw this up.</i>

4
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:12,933
<i>I'm appointing you
as the new CEO.</i>

5
00:00:13,067 --> 00:00:14,067
<i> Effective immediately.</i>

6
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:15,400
<i> No excuses.</i>

7
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:17,500
<i>I know you deserve
that position,</i>

8
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:19,133
<i> and the company needs you.</i>

9
00:00:19,267 --> 00:00:21,000
<i> Jasmine and I need you, too.</i>

10
00:00:21,133 --> 00:00:23,633
<i>One day,
this is all going to get easier.</i>

11
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:25,067
<i> We'll get there, okay?</i>

12
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,433
<i> Us. Together. As a family.</i>

13
00:00:27,567 --> 00:00:29,300
<i>- Jasmine?
- Mom?</i>

14
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:32,433
<i>I told you not to lock
your door.</i>

15
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:33,733
<i>What if something
happens to you?</i>

16
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:34,900
<i> What if there's an emergency?</i>

17
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:37,033
<i>Oh, yeah, it's our anniversary.</i>

18
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:38,200
<i>You didn't think I forgot,
did you?</i>

19
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:39,333
<i> Wait.</i>

20
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:41,933
<i>Love,
you haven't opened my gift yet.</i>

21
00:00:42,067 --> 00:00:43,233
<i> I'll be back.</i>

22
00:00:43,467 --> 00:00:47,900
<i>You always find time for your
mom, for Jobert, for Jas.</i>

23
00:00:48,033 --> 00:00:50,433
<i>I just wish
you'd find time for...</i>

24
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:54,500
Love.

25
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:56,833
Love.

26
00:01:07,033 --> 00:01:08,500
Jasmine.

27
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:10,867
Why did you leave your room?

28
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,800
Weren't you not feeling well?

29
00:01:12,933 --> 00:01:15,933
Where's Weng? I told her
to keep an eye on you.

30
00:01:16,067 --> 00:01:19,533
Mom just asked her to fix
something in their room.

31
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:21,333
What if something
happens to you?

32
00:01:21,467 --> 00:01:24,133
Oh no, your mom's
going to scold you again.

33
00:01:25,767 --> 00:01:27,567
I'm used to it, Yolly.

34
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:29,800
Is anything
ever going to change?

35
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:31,967
No matter what I do,

36
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:35,233
follow the rules, behave,

37
00:01:35,367 --> 00:01:36,933
take my medicines on time,

38
00:01:37,067 --> 00:01:38,900
they're still the same.

39
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:40,633
Mom's always...

40
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,933
hovering,

41
00:01:43,167 --> 00:01:44,733
always stressed,

42
00:01:44,867 --> 00:01:46,500
like she's carrying
the whole world.

43
00:01:46,633 --> 00:01:47,600
And dad?

44
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:50,033
He's never around.

45
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:52,400
And when he is,

46
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:55,567
he expects our whole world
to revolve around him.

47
00:01:56,867 --> 00:01:58,367
Oh, Sweetheart.

48
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:02,133
You shouldn't talk about
your parents like that.

49
00:02:02,267 --> 00:02:04,067
Whatever.

50
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,533
You're right.

51
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,100
I'll just go to sleep.

52
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:01,200
<i> You're still up?</i>

53
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:02,933
<i> It's late.</i>

54
00:03:03,067 --> 00:03:04,500
I can't sleep.

55
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:09,067
And I'm kind of shaken up.
My parents fought again.

56
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:11,967
Their schedules
don't always match.

57
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:14,400
And when it does,
they just end up fighting.

58
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:16,200
I'm so sorry, Jas.

59
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:19,000
<i>I mean, I should be used to it,
right?</i>

60
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:22,767
They never run out of reasons
to fight.

61
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,033
There's always an issue.

62
00:03:27,567 --> 00:03:29,367
And me?

63
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,267
I'm the shock absorber.

64
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:35,500
You're lucky.
Your parents seem chill.

65
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:37,300
<i> You guys are stable.</i>

66
00:03:37,433 --> 00:03:39,033
Stable?

67
00:03:39,167 --> 00:03:40,300
It's only quiet

68
00:03:40,433 --> 00:03:43,300
because you're just supposed to
automatically know everything.

69
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,733
But anyway...

70
00:03:50,867 --> 00:03:52,700
are you excited
for your birthday?

71
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:57,933
Mom's super excited.

72
00:03:58,067 --> 00:04:00,533
She planned everything.

73
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:02,467
Everything I want? Not allowed.

74
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,600
Anything fun? Not allowed.

75
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:06,800
I mean, I feel okay now.

76
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,233
But she's still super strict.

77
00:04:09,367 --> 00:04:11,100
<i> Mommy patrol alert!</i>

78
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:13,567
<i> But you know what?</i>

79
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:17,233
<i>I'm sure your party's
going to be great.</i>

80
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,733
I promise.

81
00:04:18,867 --> 00:04:21,400
It'll be even better
if you show up.

82
00:04:21,533 --> 00:04:23,767
But even if I can't make it,

83
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:27,200
you're not alone, Jas.

84
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:28,467
I'm here.

85
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:29,900
Of course.

86
00:04:30,033 --> 00:04:30,967
So?

87
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:31,867
Breathe?

88
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,967
- Ready?
- Ready when you are.

89
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:39,533
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

90
00:04:49,067 --> 00:04:50,400
- We got this.
- We got this.

91
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,167
Thank you, Weng.

92
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:06,133
<i> Just bring it to the car.</i>

93
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:07,600
Hi, Love.

94
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,067
Good morning.

95
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,800
Hi. Good morning.

96
00:05:13,333 --> 00:05:15,033
What's this?

97
00:05:15,267 --> 00:05:17,400
Just trying to make up
for last night.

98
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:21,400
Happy anniversary, Love.

99
00:05:21,533 --> 00:05:22,733
I love you.

100
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:33,500
Come on, eat.

101
00:05:36,467 --> 00:05:39,967
What do you want?
Fruits? Bread? Rice?

102
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:42,167
- Fruits.
- Okay.

103
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:46,767
Love, remember that...

104
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:48,100
lunch this weekend?

105
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:50,167
With one of our partners?

106
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:53,000
I was hoping
you'd come with me.

107
00:05:54,733 --> 00:05:56,367
Love...

108
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,400
that's the last session
with the client

109
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:00,733
who's been consulting with me.
It's online, though.

110
00:06:00,867 --> 00:06:03,667
But I'm visiting mom, too.

111
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,967
We're handling something
for Jobert.

112
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:09,900
And Jasmine has training
that afternoon.

113
00:06:10,067 --> 00:06:11,800
I need to go with her.

114
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:18,400
You know, sometimes...

115
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:21,100
I wish you were more like my mom
used to be.

116
00:06:21,233 --> 00:06:24,133
She was always with dad at...

117
00:06:24,267 --> 00:06:27,100
business meetings, brunches...

118
00:06:27,233 --> 00:06:28,333
and dinners.

119
00:06:29,533 --> 00:06:30,867
She was always there.

120
00:06:33,533 --> 00:06:34,933
Love...

121
00:06:35,067 --> 00:06:37,700
they didn't have a child
like Jasmine.

122
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:43,433
And she didn't have a mom
with issues

123
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,267
or a brother
who needed looking after.

124
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:49,433
Their life isn't our life.

125
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:51,033
So...

126
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:52,400
no?

127
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:53,933
You're not coming?

128
00:06:57,133 --> 00:07:01,067
Love, if only I could
split myself in two...

129
00:07:04,733 --> 00:07:05,867
Okay.

130
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,200
Fine.

131
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:08,767
I'm off to work.

132
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,467
Thanks for the
"consolation breakfast."

133
00:07:27,133 --> 00:07:29,600
Marj, your insights
are amazing.

134
00:07:29,733 --> 00:07:32,167
It's such a waste that
you didn't go back to sales.

135
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:34,733
You'd probably be
a top performer again.

136
00:07:34,867 --> 00:07:36,533
Thank you.

137
00:07:36,667 --> 00:07:40,700
But I'm sticking to consultancy
for now.

138
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:43,133
I really need
to focus on my family.

139
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,733
<i> Let's go, Oscar.</i>

140
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:52,000
<i> We'll just park the SUV out.</i>

141
00:07:52,133 --> 00:07:53,767
Just going to practice
inside the clubhouse.

142
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,467
Real quick.

143
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,700
Jasmine, we can't.

144
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:58,600
You don't have a license yet.

145
00:07:58,733 --> 00:08:00,967
I'll get in trouble.

146
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:03,033
You're overreacting,
Oscar.

147
00:08:03,167 --> 00:08:07,033
My friends drive themselves
to school.

148
00:08:09,467 --> 00:08:10,733
Come on.

149
00:08:10,867 --> 00:08:12,167
Just a quick spin.

150
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:14,100
I'm not going to race
or anything.

151
00:08:19,867 --> 00:08:22,167
Marj, everything okay?

152
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:25,200
Jasmine, I really can't do
what you're asking.

153
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:27,133
I'll get in serious trouble.

154
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:30,167
Relax, Oscar.
It's called practice.

155
00:08:37,867 --> 00:08:39,533
Ma'am Jasmine?

156
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:41,167
Ma'am Marj?

157
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:43,300
I just need to step out
for a bit.

158
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:44,833
I'll be right back.

159
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:45,933
Sure.

160
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:47,567
Sorry, excuse me.

161
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:01,533
- Hey, Jasmine!
- I'll be right back!

162
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:03,200
Open this!

163
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:05,567
- Hurry!
- Jasmine!

164
00:09:07,567 --> 00:09:09,533
Sweetheart. Open this door.

165
00:09:09,667 --> 00:09:10,767
Now!

166
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,600
You can't do this.
This is dangerous!

167
00:09:12,733 --> 00:09:14,500
What are you doing?

168
00:09:14,633 --> 00:09:16,633
What's going on with you?

169
00:09:16,767 --> 00:09:18,800
Mom, chill.

170
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:21,600
I'm just practicing driving.

171
00:09:21,733 --> 00:09:23,333
Everyone my age is learning.

172
00:09:23,467 --> 00:09:25,133
What if you suddenly
get out of breath?

173
00:09:25,267 --> 00:09:27,567
What if your chest tightens?

174
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:30,867
What if you pass out?

175
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,100
Mom, I'm fine.

176
00:09:32,233 --> 00:09:33,867
I've been fine for years.

177
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,800
Even my doctors say
my progress is good.

178
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:40,500
You don't know that, Jasmine.
What if something happens?

179
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:42,933
And what you're doing
is illegal!

180
00:09:43,067 --> 00:09:46,267
Progress doesn't mean
you can drive without a license!

181
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:49,167
Mom, I'm 16. Not 6.

182
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:52,433
<i>I'm not some fragile
Murano vase of grandmother.</i>

183
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,100
Where are you even going?

184
00:09:55,233 --> 00:09:56,167
To the clubhouse.

185
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:58,600
- To meet my friends.
- No!

186
00:09:58,733 --> 00:10:01,167
Not after
what you just tried to do.

187
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:03,500
If you want me to treat you
like a 16-year-old,

188
00:10:03,633 --> 00:10:05,367
then you should know
there are consequences

189
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,267
for your wrong actions.

190
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,433
<i> Wrong?</i>

191
00:10:08,667 --> 00:10:10,367
It's just practice
driving, Mom.

192
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,433
But to you,
it's automatically danger,

193
00:10:12,567 --> 00:10:14,233
disaster, emergency!

194
00:10:14,367 --> 00:10:16,233
Everything's forbidden!

195
00:10:16,367 --> 00:10:19,433
Jasmine, I'm trying
to protect you.

196
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:20,400
You know what?

197
00:10:20,533 --> 00:10:21,433
I think the problem
is you still see me

198
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:24,267
as that sick baby
in an incubator.

199
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:27,100
Can't I just be normal?
Even just for a little while?

200
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:29,200
Am I not allowed to be happy?

201
00:10:34,667 --> 00:10:36,033
Jasmine!

202
00:10:47,267 --> 00:10:49,400
This is good, Paolo.

203
00:10:49,533 --> 00:10:52,200
The traffic flow
at the entry points looks solid.

204
00:10:53,533 --> 00:10:58,767
And I like that you added
mixed-use pockets in Phase 2.

205
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:00,767
That's smart.

206
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:03,600
Property value's going to rise
faster that way.

207
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:11,000
You're usually
more engaged than this.

208
00:11:12,667 --> 00:11:16,767
Is it because you're meeting
with me and not my dad?

209
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:19,267
Are you okay?

210
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:22,967
Sorry.

211
00:11:26,067 --> 00:11:27,333
Work problem?

212
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:29,333
Or something personal?

213
00:11:36,033 --> 00:11:37,000
Marj and I.

214
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,700
We're going through something.

215
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:44,500
Oh, so the heavy part
isn't the project.

216
00:11:45,433 --> 00:11:47,033
It's your heart?

217
00:11:49,467 --> 00:11:51,400
Well...

218
00:11:51,667 --> 00:11:52,967
she's busy with our daughter.

219
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,900
I'm drowning in work.

220
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:59,700
We don't even meet
halfway anymore.

221
00:12:01,133 --> 00:12:04,667
Paolo, you can't pour
from an empty cup.

222
00:12:06,933 --> 00:12:12,667
Sometimes people need
more than responsibility.

223
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,733
They need to feel...

224
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,067
seen.

225
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:25,233
Maybe what you need is...

226
00:12:25,367 --> 00:12:26,733
a breather.

227
00:12:28,633 --> 00:12:32,733
Like old times, when we were
still single nepotism babies.

228
00:12:36,567 --> 00:12:37,900
A little distraction.

229
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:44,100
Someone who gets you.

230
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:55,833
Victoria, we're both married.

231
00:12:55,967 --> 00:12:58,433
And I'm not looking
for any distractions.

232
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:02,100
Can we please just get back
to the meeting?

233
00:13:10,033 --> 00:13:11,300
I'm so exhausted, Mom.

234
00:13:11,433 --> 00:13:14,800
Paolo and I
are still not okay.

235
00:13:14,933 --> 00:13:16,367
And my daughter...

236
00:13:17,733 --> 00:13:19,967
she feels so distant
from me now.

237
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,533
Marj...

238
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:24,900
that's family life.

239
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:27,367
Not every day is easy.

240
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:32,267
But, Mom, the hard days
are happening more often.

241
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:36,200
Stay strong, girl.

242
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:38,533
You can handle it.

243
00:13:38,867 --> 00:13:42,667
You supported your mom and
Jobert on your own, didn't you?

244
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:47,100
And, Marj,

245
00:13:47,233 --> 00:13:49,833
just be patient with Jasmine.

246
00:13:49,967 --> 00:13:51,833
<i> It's her birthday soon anyway.</i>

247
00:13:55,667 --> 00:13:57,467
- Jobert!
- Jobert?

248
00:14:01,067 --> 00:14:03,967
Marj, look at this.
Look at your brother.

249
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:06,433
This is what he's been doing.
Look, Marj.

250
00:14:06,567 --> 00:14:08,167
<i> He does that the whole day.</i>

251
00:14:14,367 --> 00:14:17,533
Jobert, that's enough.
Go rest, okay? That's enough.

252
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:20,633
-You've been doing that all day.
-No!

253
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:23,267
It's because Aunt Evelyn
keeps protecting him.

254
00:14:24,267 --> 00:14:26,267
Jobert wants space.

255
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,067
He's not a baby anymore, Marj.

256
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:33,067
But he's not allowed
to be an adult either.

257
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,567
He's struggling.

258
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,033
Jasmine?

259
00:14:41,933 --> 00:14:43,767
Why are you crying?

260
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:47,133
Nothing.

261
00:14:49,867 --> 00:14:52,567
You know your mom.

262
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:55,867
She can be a little
over-the-top when she worries.

263
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,600
Exactly.

264
00:15:01,867 --> 00:15:03,867
Why is she like that,
Grandmother?

265
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,433
I'm okay now.

266
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:09,233
Because she's paranoid,
Sweetheart.

267
00:15:11,133 --> 00:15:14,933
She means well.
But sometimes it's too much.

268
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:17,667
You know what...

269
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:18,667
you're young.

270
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,967
You should still be enjoying
your youth.

271
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:23,400
Not just "no, no, no"
all the time.

272
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:27,567
She keeps saying,
"That's not allowed.

273
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:31,000
You can't do that. It might
trigger your condition."

274
00:15:31,133 --> 00:15:33,000
Jas...

275
00:15:33,267 --> 00:15:36,833
you know your body
better than anyone, right?

276
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:39,733
You know what you can
handle and what you can't.

277
00:15:41,700 --> 00:15:46,167
But about the underage driving,
I agree with your mom on that.

278
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:47,700
That's a no.

279
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:52,900
But if you want to go out
with your friends,

280
00:15:53,933 --> 00:15:56,000
I'll allow it.

281
00:15:56,133 --> 00:15:57,967
You know, when someone's
constantly scolded

282
00:15:58,100 --> 00:16:00,367
and criticized,
they tend to rebel even more.

283
00:16:10,433 --> 00:16:12,800
No. No more.

284
00:16:12,933 --> 00:16:16,167
Big, big, big boy.
I'm a big boy now.

285
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:18,400
I don't want this
house anymore.

286
00:16:18,633 --> 00:16:20,533
I don't want school. No.

287
00:16:36,533 --> 00:16:37,400
- Really?
- Yeah.

288
00:16:37,533 --> 00:16:39,200
- I can?
- Yes, of course.

289
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:40,900
Grandmother's got your back.

290
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:43,533
- Really, Grandmother?
- Yes. Of course.

291
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:45,400
You're not going to get stressed

292
00:16:45,533 --> 00:16:47,933
just hanging out
with your friends, right?

293
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:49,167
Go. Enjoy.

294
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,033
Live a little.

295
00:16:51,167 --> 00:16:52,533
Thank you, Grandmother.

296
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:58,367
You have fun, okay?

297
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:00,433
- I will. Thank you.
- All right, go on.

298
00:17:02,033 --> 00:17:03,200
I'll be careful, I promise.

299
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:04,900
You promise, okay?

300
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:10,800
- Thank you, Grandmother.
- Have fun.

301
00:17:10,933 --> 00:17:12,567
I love you.

302
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:14,033
<i> Bye!</i>

303
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:23,833
- I had so much fun earlier.
- Yeah, me too.

304
00:17:24,067 --> 00:17:25,833
Oh my gosh, same!

305
00:17:25,967 --> 00:17:27,433
So, next time again?

306
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:28,600
Sure!

307
00:17:28,867 --> 00:17:30,033
Hit some first.

308
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,567
Sure.

309
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:44,167
Where have you been?

310
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:46,467
Excuse us.

311
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:48,100
You girls head home now, okay?

312
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:49,700
Yes, Ma'am. Bye!

313
00:17:51,267 --> 00:17:53,467
Sweetheart, where were you?

314
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,767
Just at the clubhouse, Mom.

315
00:17:55,900 --> 00:17:57,433
Just the clubhouse?

316
00:17:57,567 --> 00:17:59,300
You disobeyed me.

317
00:17:59,433 --> 00:18:01,633
Didn't I tell you
not to go out?

318
00:18:01,767 --> 00:18:03,733
I didn't drive, okay?

319
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:05,433
I just went out.

320
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:08,000
It's not illegal
to get some fresh air.

321
00:18:08,133 --> 00:18:09,567
That's not the point.

322
00:18:10,667 --> 00:18:11,967
Everything's always forbidden.

323
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:13,600
Everything I do is wrong.

324
00:18:13,733 --> 00:18:16,967
Even just hanging out with
my friends is not allowed?

325
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:22,167
Jasmine, that's not the point.

326
00:18:22,433 --> 00:18:26,100
I grounded you because
you did something wrong earlier.

327
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:28,667
Grandmother said I could go.

328
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:30,533
So why is it only your rules
that matter?

329
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:33,000
What?

330
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:35,267
If it's not healthy,
it's not allowed.

331
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:37,400
If it's not by the rules,
it's not allowed.

332
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:39,433
If it's not on your timeline,
it's not allowed.

333
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:41,767
Even if grandmother already
said yes, it's still no?

334
00:18:44,133 --> 00:18:48,233
Mom, not everything I do
is the end of the world.

335
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:52,900
Jasmine.

336
00:19:01,967 --> 00:19:02,933
Excuse me, Mom.

337
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:07,100
I heard you let Jasmine go out

338
00:19:07,233 --> 00:19:08,667
even after
I already told her no?

339
00:19:10,033 --> 00:19:11,833
Yes. I did.

340
00:19:12,867 --> 00:19:14,933
I felt bad for her.

341
00:19:15,067 --> 00:19:18,200
She looked like a bird
dying to stretch her wings.

342
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,733
Mom, that's not okay.

343
00:19:21,867 --> 00:19:22,933
She did something wrong.

344
00:19:23,067 --> 00:19:25,333
That's why
we're disciplining her.

345
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:30,100
And you know
she can't just go out anytime

346
00:19:30,267 --> 00:19:32,467
because of her condition.

347
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,367
Oh my gosh, Marj.

348
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:35,167
She just wanted
to see her friends.

349
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,867
What's so wrong with that?

350
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:38,400
What is she, one of my
porcelain collectibles?

351
00:19:38,533 --> 00:19:40,500
Does she have a
"handle with extreme care" label

352
00:19:40,633 --> 00:19:43,500
on her forehead? No, right?

353
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:47,700
I'm protecting my daughter, Mom.

354
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:51,833
I know her body.
I know what could harm her.

355
00:19:53,767 --> 00:19:56,300
Protecting her?
Or imprisoning her?

356
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,867
Marj, ask yourself that.

357
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,133
There's a very fine line,

358
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:05,067
and you're dancing
on the wrong side of it.

359
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:08,967
Mom, please.

360
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,467
I'm trying my best.

361
00:20:12,633 --> 00:20:15,400
So please, support me.

362
00:20:15,533 --> 00:20:18,767
I know you think
you're doing your best.

363
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:20,900
But that doesn't mean
you're doing it right.

364
00:20:21,233 --> 00:20:23,100
Let me remind you, Marj.

365
00:20:23,233 --> 00:20:25,000
Jasmine is my granddaughter.

366
00:20:25,133 --> 00:20:26,933
I love her, too.

367
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:28,800
And you can't stop me

368
00:20:28,933 --> 00:20:32,600
from saving her every time
she feels suffocated by you.

369
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:41,100
I'm still Jasmine's mother.

370
00:20:41,233 --> 00:20:45,200
If you want to help
raise my child,

371
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:47,833
then we need to be consistent.

372
00:20:47,967 --> 00:20:50,400
Not you saying yes
whenever you feel like it,

373
00:20:50,533 --> 00:20:53,600
and me dealing
with the consequences.

374
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,600
Consistent?

375
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:57,700
Consistent in fear?

376
00:20:58,033 --> 00:21:00,633
Consistent in restrictions?

377
00:21:00,933 --> 00:21:02,200
If that's your version
of consistency,

378
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:06,433
then I don't want
to be part of it.

379
00:21:06,567 --> 00:21:08,033
Maybe you should reflect, Marj.

380
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:11,833
Maybe you've forgotten
how to let her live.

381
00:21:11,967 --> 00:21:14,200
Maybe it's you
who's holding her back

382
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:16,400
and not her condition anymore.

383
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:22,667
Mom. Marj.

384
00:21:24,433 --> 00:21:25,467
What's going on?

385
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:27,767
Paolo,

386
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:29,767
I just let Jasmine go out

387
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:31,833
because my poor granddaughter
looked so lonely.

388
00:21:31,967 --> 00:21:34,533
I just wanted to make her happy,
even just for a little while.

389
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:38,433
Paolo, I was just explaining
to mom

390
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:40,833
what's not allowed
for our daughter.

391
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,933
But they went against me.

392
00:21:45,033 --> 00:21:47,333
Did she have an episode?

393
00:21:47,467 --> 00:21:49,467
Did she start wheezing?

394
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:50,933
Did her chest tighten?

395
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:56,000
No.

396
00:21:56,133 --> 00:21:57,167
- She's fine.
- See?

397
00:21:57,300 --> 00:21:59,267
You're just being paranoid.

398
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,833
Mom!

399
00:22:03,300 --> 00:22:04,400
Marj...

400
00:22:04,533 --> 00:22:06,467
let's not make a big deal
out of this.

401
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,367
Especially if Jas is okay.

402
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:15,733
So, because nothing
happened, that's it?

403
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,267
We just bend the rules?

404
00:22:18,933 --> 00:22:20,700
Is that how it works, Paolo?

405
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:22,900
Marj, it's not like that.

406
00:22:24,333 --> 00:22:26,700
I just don't want us to...

407
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:28,267
overreact.

408
00:22:34,033 --> 00:22:35,400
Rose?

409
00:22:36,433 --> 00:22:38,633
Can you bring me my tea?

410
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:53,467
Drink some water first, dear.

411
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:06,067
So what?

412
00:23:07,467 --> 00:23:09,733
Now it's my fault
they're fighting?

413
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:16,000
Just try to understand your mom
if she's strict sometimes.

414
00:23:17,133 --> 00:23:19,900
Not sometimes.

415
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:21,367
All the time.

416
00:23:22,533 --> 00:23:24,200
I'm almost 16, Yolly.

417
00:23:25,467 --> 00:23:28,033
I can take care of myself.

418
00:23:28,167 --> 00:23:29,667
I know my limits.

419
00:23:31,133 --> 00:23:33,633
Why does it feel like...

420
00:23:33,767 --> 00:23:36,900
every single move I make
still has to be monitored?

421
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:44,767
Jasmine...

422
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:49,133
you didn't see what your mom
went through before.

423
00:23:51,067 --> 00:23:53,400
The nights she couldn't sleep

424
00:23:53,533 --> 00:23:55,267
because she was watching
over you.

425
00:23:57,267 --> 00:23:59,967
When she'd see you
struggling to breathe,

426
00:24:01,467 --> 00:24:03,433
every beep of that machine...

427
00:24:04,967 --> 00:24:09,000
Dear, your mom felt like
her whole world was collapsing.

428
00:24:11,233 --> 00:24:13,967
Yes, she's strict.

429
00:24:15,533 --> 00:24:17,767
But...

430
00:24:18,033 --> 00:24:21,800
she's not doing that because she
doesn't want you to be happy.

431
00:24:23,067 --> 00:24:26,867
She's doing it because
she's terrified of losing you.

432
00:24:43,067 --> 00:24:45,200
So now I'm the one overreacting?

433
00:24:45,967 --> 00:24:49,200
Paolo, I'm the one with our
daughter every single night!

434
00:24:49,333 --> 00:24:52,167
I'm the one who saw her struggle
to breathe.

435
00:24:52,300 --> 00:24:54,333
I'm the one who prayed
she'd make it to 16,

436
00:24:54,467 --> 00:24:56,233
and now I'm the dramatic one?

437
00:24:57,767 --> 00:24:59,700
Marj...

438
00:24:59,933 --> 00:25:02,933
maybe you should try
letting her breathe.

439
00:25:03,267 --> 00:25:04,367
Give her some slack.

440
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:07,000
Don't be so hyper-focused
on her.

441
00:25:07,233 --> 00:25:09,300
You might be neglecting
something else.

442
00:25:11,933 --> 00:25:13,233
Neglecting?

443
00:25:14,267 --> 00:25:15,667
Who?

444
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:17,767
You?

445
00:25:17,900 --> 00:25:19,733
So now you're turning this on me
again.

446
00:25:19,867 --> 00:25:23,000
That I'm neglecting you, Paolo?

447
00:25:23,133 --> 00:25:26,300
I don't need another person
to take care of!

448
00:25:26,433 --> 00:25:27,300
Can't you see?

449
00:25:27,433 --> 00:25:29,933
I already have
so much on my plate.

450
00:25:30,067 --> 00:25:34,067
My mom, Jobert,
the house, Jasmine!

451
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:36,500
But what about me?

452
00:25:36,667 --> 00:25:38,800
Who takes care of me?

453
00:25:40,233 --> 00:25:42,433
I'm not saying it like that.

454
00:25:43,433 --> 00:25:45,300
I'm on your side.

455
00:25:45,433 --> 00:25:46,733
It should be me.

456
00:25:49,333 --> 00:25:53,167
So why do you feel
like another burden?

457
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:55,567
Why am I the one who's wrong?

458
00:25:55,700 --> 00:25:57,433
Why am I the one who's too much?

459
00:26:02,567 --> 00:26:04,233
Where's the Marj
I fell in love with?

460
00:26:05,867 --> 00:26:09,100
Where's the Marj who had
everything together?

461
00:26:09,267 --> 00:26:11,833
Not the mom whose whole world
revolves around Jasmine

462
00:26:11,967 --> 00:26:14,233
and every responsibility
on Earth.

463
00:26:17,267 --> 00:26:19,967
You want to see the Marj
you fell in love with?

464
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:21,500
How?

465
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:24,567
When was the last time
you chose to stand beside me?

466
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:30,267
When was the last time
you actually understood me?

467
00:26:35,900 --> 00:26:38,700
Surprise! Happy birthday!

468
00:26:38,833 --> 00:26:41,000
Make a wish,
even if it's just virtual.

469
00:26:41,133 --> 00:26:42,800
I really wish you could come.

470
00:26:42,967 --> 00:26:45,033
Are you ready
for your party tonight?

471
00:26:45,167 --> 00:26:47,833
I know things
haven't been easy lately,

472
00:26:48,067 --> 00:26:50,100
and maybe I've been a little
too much.

473
00:26:50,233 --> 00:26:51,400
I won't stop you

474
00:26:51,533 --> 00:26:53,733
from doing everything you want
to do anymore.

475
00:26:53,867 --> 00:26:57,600
Sixteen candles, sixteen wishes.

476
00:26:57,733 --> 00:27:01,767
But honestly, I only want one.

477
00:27:01,900 --> 00:27:03,333
Space.

478
00:27:03,467 --> 00:27:04,633
For me.

479
00:27:04,767 --> 00:27:06,000
For my family.

480
00:27:06,133 --> 00:27:07,133
Jasmine!

481
00:27:08,667 --> 00:27:10,067
Ash!

482
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:13,433
Ash, where are uncle and aunt?

483
00:27:17,967 --> 00:27:19,900
Hi, Marj!
